                    <msContents>
                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>Achchutayadēva-mahārāya Ś. 1459: 1537 A.D.</p>						
                            
                            <p>The details of date given in this inscription, viz., Ś. 1459, Hēviḷambi, Makara, ēkā, daśi, Friday, Saṅkramaṇa, correspond to 1537 A.D., December 28.</p>						
                            
                            <p>It records the gift of money for day and <hi rend="italic">sandhi</hi> lamps, garland, unguents and <hi rend="italic">tirupa parivaṭṭam</hi> to god Chidamba[ra] Īśvaramuḍaiya Nayiṉār and worship and services to god Koppuṉāthapperumāḷ and Sōmanāthar on the hill at Chandragiri in Vaikundavaḷanāḍu in Tiruveṅgaḍa-kōṭṭam in Jayaṅgoṇḍaśōḻa-maṇḍalam for the merit of the king by Achchutarāya Nāyakkar, the <hi rend="italic">durgādhipati</hi> of Chandra[giri].</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
